Rev Python 0bf &ldquo;You don&rsquo;t need to deobfuscate the Python, but that&rsquo;s up to you. ;-;&rdquo;
We are given a python file that obfuscates some data. Write a small script to undo the same operations (reverse string, base64 decode, zlib decompress), and repeat until flag is found.

Crypto My Magic Bytes &ldquo;Can you recover the secret XOR key we used to encrypt the flag?&rdquo;
Knowing the properties of XOR and the magic bytes for a jpg, we can recover the key by XORing the beginning bytes of the file with FF D8 FF E0 00 10 4A 46 49 46 00 01
Then with the following script, we XOR the key with the file. The result of this is an image which has the flag!
